sentence: Consumer stocks were rising Thursday, joining with gains for the broader markets today.

In company news, ConAgra ( CAG ) advanced Thursday after the processed and packaged foods company late yesterday increased the size of its board to 14 members, naming two new directors affiliated with Jana Partners LLC as part of a broader agreement with the activist investors.
Joining the ConAgra board later this month will be Bradley Alford and Timothy McLevish.
Alford is the former chief executive of Nestle USA while McLevish was the chief financial officer at Walgreens Boots Alliance ( WBA ).

The board additions follow the company last week announce plans to shed its struggling private-label business as well as considering other strategic actions, moves Jana has publicly advocated since disclosing a 7.1% ConAgra ownership stake and threatening a potential proxy fight for three board seats up for election this year.
Jana also accepted to a standstill agreement to keep from future public spats with ConAgra management for at least the next year.
CAG shares were up almost 1% at $44.99 each, easing from an earlier run to $45.32 a share.
The stock already had risen more than 46% over the past 12 months before today's price gain, closing at an all-time high of $45.49 a share on Tuesday.
